net.openhft.chronicle.map

Interface UnaryOperator<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the mutable input
    All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable

    public interface UnaryOperator<T>
extends Serializable
    Represents a mutator that accepts one mutable argument, which it may alter and produces a result.

    This is not functional as it can alter an argument.
